# Optional: override voice API when not using the /api reverse proxy (e.g. direct backend URL).
# REACT_APP_VOICE_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api/voice/extract

# Local dev (npm start): package.json "proxy" forwards /api/* to http://localhost:8080
# Container runtime: set VOICE_API_BACKEND to the voice service origin (no /api suffix path needed in env)
#   docker run -e VOICE_API_BACKEND=http://voice-api:8080 -p 8080:80 quay.io/mklaasse/frida-carclaims-frontend
#   → browser calls /api/voice/extract → nginx proxies to http://voice-api:8080/api/voice/extract

# Manual test plan:
# 1. Start backend on :8080, run npm start
# 2. Open /accident step, tap mic FAB, speak, tap green check
# 3. Verify fields populate from response claimsData
# 4. Navigate forward/back — voice data persists via sessionStorage
# Note: Microphone requires HTTPS in production (localhost is exempt).
